Here are some common JSON examples related to "moms" (mothers), depending on what you're looking for:

### 1. **Basic Mom Profile (JSON Object)**
```json
{
  "name": "Sarah Johnson",
  "age": 35,
  "children": [
    {
      "name": "Emma",
      "age": 8
    },
    {
      "name": "Liam",
      "age": 5
    }
  ],
  "occupation": "Teacher",
  "hobbies": ["reading", "gardening", "cooking"]
}
```

### 2. **List of Moms (JSON Array)**
```json
[
  {
    "name": "Maria Garcia",
    "age": 29,
    "children_count": 1
  },
  {
    "name": "Aisha Khan",
    "age": 42,
    "children_count": 3
  },
  {
    "name": "Yuki Tanaka",
    "age": 31,
    "children_count": 2
  }
]
```

### 3. **Mom’s Daily Schedule**
```json
{
  "name": "Lisa Brown",
  "schedule": {
    "morning": ["wake up at 6 AM", "prepare breakfast", "drop kids at school"],
    "afternoon": ["work (remote)", "lunch", "grocery shopping"],
    "evening": ["pick up kids", "cook dinner", "help with homework"],
    "night": ["bedtime stories", "relax", "sleep at 10 PM"]
  }
}
```

### 4. **Mom’s Shopping List**
```json
{
  "mom_name": "Priya Patel",
  "shopping_list": [
    {"item": "Milk", "quantity": "2 liters"},
    {"item": "Eggs", "quantity": "1 dozen"},
    {"item": "Bread", "quantity": "1 loaf"},
    {"item": "Fruits", "quantity": "apples, bananas"},
    {"item": "Diapers", "quantity": "1 pack (size 3)"}
  ]
}
```

### 5. **Mom’s Contact Info (for an app)**
```json
{
  "id": 101,
  "name": "Jennifer Lee",
  "email": "jennifer.lee@example.com",
  "phone": "+1-555-123-4567",
  "emergency_contact": {
    "name": "David Lee (Husband)",
    "phone": "+1-555-987-6543"
  }
}
```
